 lovers in brain scanners. Geneticists reconstruct the sex crimes of Genghis Khan. Neuroscientists create mice whose sexual behavior can be switched on and off. A zoologist traps and releases 260,000 voles and launches a new science of love.LeVay distills vast expertise on the biology and psychology of sex into an engaging and easy-to-understand survey with scientific acumen, a critical eye, and a sense of humor. This book reveals how scientists are unraveling the secrets of sex and, in the process, shattering many traditional ideas and prejudices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aSex (Biology). 0aSex (Psychology). 0aSex. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Evolution.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074967008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131921608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023z9783111318615oZDB-23-DPM40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/leva2045040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231555579423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231555579/original  a978-3-11-074967-0  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131921-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DPMb2023